http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/New-vehicles-for-police-department/article13985717.ece

The Police Department is set to acquire 560 new vehicles at an estimated cost of Rs. 42.2 crore, Home Minister Ramesh Chennithala said in a press release here on Wednesday.The police would require to phase out 1,388 vehicles soon and this was the first instalment of purchase.Some 160 vehicles would be allotted to police station houses. About 100 vehicles have been earmarked for field operations and high range areas. Control rooms will be given 70 vans. Another 80 vans will be given to units involved in anti-naxal operations.Armed police battalions and special units would also be given new vehicles.